<div id="review_3425109171" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3425109171" />
    <a title="Nikhil" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81954991-nikhil"><img alt="Nikhil" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607539111p2/81954991.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3425109171?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nikhil" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nikhil" href="/user/show/81954991-nikhil">Nikhil</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3425109171" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3210119986511332432">Quite refreshing. <br/>Though, I didn&apos;t enjoy the Draupadi and Karan&apos;s angle. It was just not convincing enough. But then these were the thoughts of Draupadi according to the author and can&apos;t be questioned. <br/>Another angle of Draupadi and Kunti was portrayed quite convincingly and the events totally justified Draupadi&apos;s thoughts for Kunti. <br/>I was expecting more of Draupadi in this book but I guess the author has made an attempt to narrate the Mahabharat through the protagonist. The entire epic is covere</span>
  <span id="freeText3210119986511332432" style="display:none">Quite refreshing. <br />Though, I didn't enjoy the Draupadi and Karan's angle. It was just not convincing enough. But then these were the thoughts of Draupadi according to the author and can't be questioned. <br />Another angle of Draupadi and Kunti was portrayed quite convincingly and the events totally justified Draupadi's thoughts for Kunti. <br />I was expecting more of Draupadi in this book but I guess the author has made an attempt to narrate the Mahabharat through the protagonist. The entire epic is covered in just 360 pages and is written beautifully with all the major events covered (which is commendable.)</span>
