<div id="review_1051958774" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1051958774" />
    <a title="Rebecca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17612864-rebecca"><img alt="Rebecca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1453456886p2/17612864.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1051958774?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca" href="/user/show/17612864-rebecca">Rebecca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17612864-rebecca?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17612864-rebecca?shelf=2017-reads">2017-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17612864-rebecca?shelf=indian">indian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17612864-rebecca?shelf=indian-challenge-2017">indian-challenge-2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1051958774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5547741535671107135">A fantastic read. Except for that twist in Draupadi&apos;s love life it would have been perfect. The stories of Mahabharatha were a part of my growing up. But i had never paused to think about what the people involved really felt and thought. So it was a surprise to read about Draupadi&apos;s feelings in her own words. What did a woman who was born from fire think about herself. ? What did she feel when she knew that she would have to marry five men ? Thete were times when I found my heart racing like whe</span>
  <span id="freeText5547741535671107135" style="display:none">A fantastic read. Except for that twist in Draupadi's love life it would have been perfect. The stories of Mahabharatha were a part of my growing up. But i had never paused to think about what the people involved really felt and thought. So it was a surprise to read about Draupadi's feelings in her own words. What did a woman who was born from fire think about herself. ? What did she feel when she knew that she would have to marry five men ? Thete were times when I found my heart racing like when I read the famous Vastrakshepam scene. All the characters have been shown in shades of grey true to the original Mahabharatha. My favourites were not the Pandus but Krishna and Bheeshma. Loved the narration. Will be sure to read more of Devakaruni.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5547741535671107135" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


